  <termversion>3.0.1</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2020-03-30</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>The mole, symbol mol, is the SI unit of amount of substance. One mole contains exactly 6.022 140 76 x 1023 elementary entities. This number is the fixed numerical value of the Avogadro constant, NA, when expressed in the unit mol-1 and is called the Avogadro number.

The amount of substance, symbol n, of a system is a measure of the number of specified elementary entities. An elementary entity may be an atom, a molecule, an ion, an electron, any other particle or specified group of particles.</text>
      <notes>
        <item>The formulation of this definition was agreed upon by the 26th CGPM in November 2018 with effect from 20 May 2019.</item>
      </notes>
